[3] France, Vendee, bat
Date: Sun 7 Jul 2016, 10:56
Source: France3-regions (Pays de la Loire) [in French, trans. Corr.SB, edited]
http://bit.ly/29NIUkO


A case of rabies has been detected in a bat at Fontenay-le-Comte (Vendee France). The infected bat was discovered in a weakened condition on 26 Jun 2016 in the gardens of the Post, by a passer-by who took it to a veterinarian.

Bat is the common name given to the flying mammals that constitute the order of bats or Cheiroptera.

[Byline: Claude Bouchet]

